---
import ToolLayout from '@/components/tools/ToolLayout.astro';
import ToolCta from '@/components/tools/ToolCta.astro';
import CostCalculator from '@/components/tools/CostCalculator';
import { tools } from '@/data/tools';

const tool = tools.find((t) => t.slug === 'webflow-cost-calculator')!;
---
<ToolLayout tool={tool}>
  <CostCalculator client:load />

  <div slot="body" class="prose-page">
    <h2>How this calculator estimates Webflow cost</h2>
    <p>
      Webflow projects split across four variables that move the price more than anything else:
      the number of pages, whether you need a CMS and how complex, whether you're migrating
      from another platform, and the SEO depth you want baked in at launch.
    </p>
    <p>
      The estimate above blends agency rates ($150–$250/hour) with freelance rates ($60–$100/hour)
      across those four variables. It lands on a range rather than a single number because the
      real cost depends on designer handoff quality, how many reviews you need, and whether
      copy is final at kickoff.
    </p>

    <h2>Typical Webflow project costs</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Landing page (1–3 pages):</strong> $800 – $2,500</li>
      <li><strong>Marketing site (5–12 pages):</strong> $2,500 – $8,000</li>
      <li><strong>Marketing site with CMS (12–25 pages):</strong> $6,000 – $15,000</li>
      <li><strong>Multi-language / multi-collection build:</strong> $15,000+</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>When a monthly retainer beats per-project pricing</h2>
    <p>
      If you are shipping more than three changes a month or constantly adding pages, a flat
      $1,999/month retainer tends to beat per-project billing once you account for scoping time,
      context-switching, and back-and-forth.
    </p>

    <ToolCta />
  </div>
</ToolLayout>
